# NPM registry configuration (optional)
# Copy this file to `.npmrc` in the repo root (or merge into `~/.npmrc`).
# `.npmrc` is gitignored so tokens and machine-specific settings stay local.

# Example: use your organization’s private npm registry (replace host and path).
# registry=https://YOUR_REGISTRY_HOST/npm/YOUR_REPO_KEY/

# Default when no .npmrc is present: the public npm registry.
# registry=https://registry.npmjs.org/

# If your registry requires authentication:
#
# always-auth=true
# //YOUR_REGISTRY_HOST/path/to/npm/repo/:_authToken=${NPM_TOKEN}

# Then run: npm install
